#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:3
#: 3d0fa5c4981843a5ac3ba5f75948f8c8
msgid "How to use the hardware compatibility list (HCL)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:6
#: 89b6f65275d64336a5198d25920fed7a
msgid ""
"The `HCL <https://www.qubes-os.org/hcl/>`__ is a compilation of reports "
"generated and submitted by users across various Qubes versions about "
"their hardware’s compatibility with Qubes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:8
#: 52bf9de6e49d4d25b6c7a8317ce470d2
msgid ""
"**Note:** Except in the case of developer-reported entries, the Qubes "
"team has not independently verified the accuracy of these reports. Please"
" first consult the data sheets (CPU, chipset, motherboard) prior to "
"buying new hardware for Qubes. Make sure it meets the :doc:`System "
"Requirements </user/hardware/system-requirements>` and search in "
"particular for support of:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:10
#: 8d334a8224f14a38adb959d7585b79ab
msgid ""
"HVM (“AMD virtualization (AMD-V)”, “Intel virtualization (VT-x)”, “VIA "
"virtualization (VIA VT)”)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:12
#: 8692ba33609f45fcaf5ef316faf9176f
msgid ""
"IOMMU (“AMD I/O Virtualization Technology (AMD-Vi)”, “Intel "
"Virtualization Technology for Directed I/O (VT-d)”)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:14
#: 8fc79929fd3a49eaac5ce6c5f0e96c3b
msgid ""
"TPM (“Trusted Platform Module (TPM)” connected to a “20-pin TPM header” "
"on motherboards.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:18
#: 6d24f65d9d324ac4b13ac6a735a73678
msgid ""
"If using the list to make a purchasing decision, we recommend that you "
"choose hardware with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:20
#: 14f390e28c3b4a0b985c474496b05bc3
msgid ""
"the best achievable Qubes security level (green columns in HVM, IOMMU, "
"TPM)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:22
#: a64da1aa5c854b39938788f3866b46b2
msgid ""
"and general machine compatibility (green columns in Qubes version, dom0 "
"kernel, remarks)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:26
#: c1099d3b8cb3460a9648df13cf92f2da
msgid ""
"Also see :doc:`Certified Hardware </user/hardware/certified-hardware"
"/certified-hardware>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:29
#: 2594be18dab442f8acfd293fda512646
msgid "Generating and Submitting New Reports"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:32
#: 01d8266fd15a4a92987fa49817486b40
msgid ""
"In order to generate an HCL report in Qubes, simply open a terminal in "
"dom0 (Applications Menu > Terminal Emulator) and run ``qubes-hcl-report "
"<qube-name>``, where ``<qube-name>`` is the name of the qube in which the"
" generated HCL files will be saved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:34
#: 4cc7b7f233734bcf85f7ecfa07f755cc
msgid ""
"You are encouraged to submit your HCL report for the benefit of further "
"Qubes development and other users. When submitting reports, test the "
"hardware yourself, if possible. If you would like to submit your HCL "
"report, please copy and paste the contents of the **HCL Info** ``.yml`` "
"file into an email to the :ref:`qubes-users mailing list "
"<introduction/support:qubes-users>` with the subject ``HCL - <your "
"machine model name>``, or create a post in the `HCL Reports category "
"<https://forum.qubes-os.org/c/user-support/hcl-reports/23>`__ of the "
"forum. Pasting the contents into the email or post has the advantage that"
" members of the mailing list and the forum can see the report without "
"downloading and opening a file. In addition, new forum members are unable"
" to attach files to posts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:36
#: 10ca761de6844043bbad0cdd9ac82e59
msgid ""
"Please include any useful information about any Qubes features you may "
"have tested (see the legend below), as well as general machine "
"compatibility (video, networking, sleep, etc.). Please consider sending "
"the **HCL Support Files** ``.cpio.gz`` file as well. To generate these "
"add the ``-s`` or ``--support`` command line option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/hardware/how-to-use-the-hcl.rst:38
#: 06d2b7f743424f529b36e9346e16acb7
msgid ""
"**Please note:** The **HCL Support Files** may contain numerous hardware "
"details, including serial numbers. If, for privacy or security reasons, "
"you do not wish to make this information public, please **do not** post "
"the ``.cpio.gz`` file on a public mailing list or forum."
msgstr ""

